Files taken (verbatim, byte-identical to upstream include/)
-----------------------------------------------------------
  A64.h                 <- Emu68 include/A64.h
      The self-contained AArch64 instruction emitter: `static inline uint32_t`
      encoders (mov_immed_u16, movk, add_reg, ret/bx_lr, ...). This is the single
      high-value asset the [J0] decision adopts. Lines 1..650 (the `#ifndef _A64_H`
      body) are pure encoders depending only on <stdint.h>. The section after
      line 650 (`#include <RegisterAllocator.h>` + the EMIT_* register-allocator
      helpers) is NOT used by the [J2] spike; it is present only because the file
      is kept verbatim.

  RegisterAllocator.h   <- Emu68 include/RegisterAllocator.h
      Declarations-only header (the RA_*/EMIT_* register-allocator interface).
      Vendored solely so that A64.h's verbatim `#include <RegisterAllocator.h>`
      (line 652) resolves and the file compiles unmodified. NONE of these RA_*
      functions are defined or called by the [J2] spike — the spike hand-emits
      without a register allocator. Full register-allocator adoption is [J3] scope.

